  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function add_data(attr_type: Number(gulong), value: ByteArray): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for gck_builder_add_data()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Add a new attribute to the builder with an arbitrary value. Unconditionally
adds a new attribute, even if one with the same <code>attr_type</code> already exists.</p>  <p>The memory in <code>value</code> is copied by the builder.</p>  <p><code>null</code> may be specified for the <code>value</code> argument, in which case an empty
attribute is created. GCK_INVALID may be specified for the length, in
which case an invalid attribute is created in the PKCS\#11 style.</p>

